Each perfusionist is expected to remain until the schedule allows for dismissal in order of arrival.Common diagnosis / Types of patients:  Case load is a mix of CABG, Valves, Root Replacements, Cardiac Anomalies (adult).  Convergent, TAVR coverage.  Occasional trauma cases.Common Type of Equipment used:  Current equipment includes Sorin/LivaNova S-5 Heart-Lung Machines with CP-5 Centrifugal Pump, Sorin/LivaNova 3T Heater/Coolers, Medtronic Autolog Cell Savers.  Maquet CS100 IABPs.Additional Notes:  Responsibilities also include maintenance of Perfusion Department equipment and stock items.  Charting and documentation of all perfusion related items.
